        <h1><span>THE</span> HISTORY</h1>
        <p>From time to time, the Magpul Design and Engineering Staff engages in “Design Exercises”, tackling design challenges outside the field of firearms and firearms accessories.  We do this so that Magpul designs stay innovative and because there is value to understanding the relationship that various design elements have with the end user across various industries.  In doing this, we aim to capture the brightest elements of a broad range of solutions to bring our customers the best possible products.</p>

        <p>The “Magpul Ronin” was one such design exercise from the fall of 2009.  The staff at Magpul, always fans of American-Made products, took interest in the Buell line of motorcycles, culminating with the Buell 1125 series.  Wondering where the platform could go under the efforts of the team, several motorcycles were purchased when Buell ceased production in the fall of 2009.  From this design exercise came the “Magpul Ronin”, a concept piece which was shown at SHOT show 2010.  There was never any intent to produce the motorcycle, but it was merely presented for what it was...a design piece. </p>

